<BaseLayout title="Affiliate Disclosure — ReviewBoard" description="ReviewBoard affiliate disclosure explaining our relationship with affiliate partners." canonical="https://reviewboard.pages.dev/affiliate-disclosure/">
  <article class="legal">
    <h1>Affiliate Disclosure</h1>
    <p><em>Last updated: June 2026</em></p>

    <p>ReviewBoard is committed to transparency. This page explains our affiliate relationships and how they work.</p>

    <h2>What Are Affiliate Links?</h2>
    <p>Some of the links on ReviewBoard are affiliate links. If you click on an affiliate link and make a purchase, ReviewBoard may earn a commission at no additional cost to you. These commissions help us maintain and operate this website.</p>

    <h2>Our Commitment to Honest Reviews</h2>
    <p>Affiliate compensation does not influence our reviews, opinions, or recommendations. We evaluate products based on research, publicly available information, and editorial judgment. We do not accept payment for positive reviews.</p>

    <h2>How We Identify Affiliate Links</h2>
    <p>Affiliate links are used throughout our content. We clearly mark pages that contain affiliate links with a disclosure notice near the top of the page.</p>

    <h2>No Additional Cost to You</h2>
    <p>Using an affiliate link does not increase the price you pay for any product or service. In some cases, we may negotiate exclusive discounts for our readers.</p>

    <h2>Questions</h2>
    <p>If you have any questions about our affiliate relationships, please <a href="/contact">contact us</a>.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .legal h1 { font-size: 2.25rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .legal h2 { margin-top: 2rem; }
  .legal p { margin: 0.75rem 0; line-height: 1.7; }
</style>
